cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper is about generating data-driven documents to report code quality, which is a key aspect of software engineering. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses software metrics and code quality, which are related to programming languages. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses natural language generation to create textual explanations about code quality. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper discusses an interaction model that allows users to explore code quality with consistent linking between text and visualizations. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses how the concept of interactive documents could generalize to multivariate data.
